 to bluff aggressively; instead, they’ll aim for clearly positive expected value trades when their turn arrives and decline proposals that look like they give up too much subjective value. Overall, we should expect: (1) few, if any, dominated trades; (2) some red/blue flowing out of Kangaroo toward Butterfly and Squid in exchange for green; (3) Butterfly and Squid sometimes competing implicitly for beneficial trades with Kangaroo; and (4) a modest number of accepted trades, biased toward clearly mutually beneficial ratios once some information has been revealed by early round behavior.",
