geted, with somewhat better surplus extraction.\n- Round 2: Final adjustments. Each player focuses on fine-tuning portfolios toward their top-valued chips, trading off green and their least valued colors where they can. Because this is a standalone game with no future reputation concerns, late-round proposals can be a bit more one-sided but still need to be individually beneficial to get accepted. By the end, it is plausible that purple is concentrated with Butterfly, red/blue with Lion and Camel, and green somewhat redistributed as the balancing medium.\n\nThe forecast below provides one coherent and internally consistent trajectory that fits the rules, personas, and value structure: early cautious probing trades around green, followed by more confident, inequality-tolerant but mutually beneficial exchanges that improve everyone’s portfolios relative to their starting bundles.",
