g clear comparative advantage lines (e.g., otter or peacock giving RED to squid, squid or otter giving BLUE to peacock, otter shedding PURPLE), but also several declined offers as players avoid being the “sucker” in trades they can’t fully evaluate. Early rounds are for information and probing; later rounds may show modest adjustments based on inferred preferences, but not full efficiency, given the time limit and incomplete information.",
