ent, structured, and somewhat uncertainty-averse: she may look for clearly positive, relatively balanced exchanges and avoid trades that look lopsided or strategically opaque. Ram is cooperative and norm-sensitive with high behavioral stability: he tends to reciprocate and avoid exploitative looking deals, but he is also alert to being taken advantage of.\n\nThe large, publicly known common range ($0.10–$1.00) for the non-green chips, combined with asymmetric private values, creates uncertainty about the exact gains from trade for others. Players only know their own valuations and must guess whether a partner’s value for a given color is high or low. Given the limited horizon and simple trading rule, we expect a few mutually beneficial, moderately generous trades—especially involving exchanging low-value BLUE for someone into high-value PURPLE or RED—mixed with some declined offers that either give too little surplus to the responder or look too speculative. Over three rounds, players will likely make their first offers somewhat cautiously, then refine later proposals using the revealed pattern of acceptances and rejections, while still constrained by the short game length and random resolution when multiple partners accept.",
